div.p:
But becauſe theſe two are made up by one action and motion, we ſhall therefore handle them together; and the ſum is this, That God by an holy kinde of violence (which is called Drawing, Iohn 6. 44. Joh. 6. 44.) doth pluck the ſoul from thoſe ſins that harbor in it unto himſelf: wherein we may conſider two things;
1. What the nature of this drawing is.
2. The means whereby God draws.
